The paper discusses techniques and results related to equivalence checking on infinite-state systems, which involves formal verification of properties of systems with infinite state spaces. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL, cs.LT), and software engineering (cs.SE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
